43e141f","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fa832ffa4e20c9aa05ac272214d43196?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fa832ffa4e20c9aa05ac272214d43196?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fa832ffa4e20c9aa05ac272214d43196?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fa832ffa4e20c9aa05ac272214d43196?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Vasiliy Kochergin","active":false,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"updated":"2016-03-24T16:48:33.083-0500","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/10001","description":"This issue has been validated/reproduced, but has not been prioritized yet.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Confirmed","id":"10001","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/2","id":2,"key":"new","colorName":"blue-gray","name":"To Do"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10003","id":"10003","name":"Cluster Controller"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10010","id":"10010","name":"Node Controller"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"Refiled and elaborated from RT-1616: https://support.eucalyptus.com/Ticket/Display.html?id=1616\r\n\r\nCurrently errors during the processing of web-services requests in the axis2c stack are reported in-line using a special purpose field from an otherwise successful response type.\r\n\r\nA number of problems result on the requestor side:\r\n# Fault classification is difficult (strings are opaque)\r\n# Fault processing becomes a source of errors (potential for null-dereferences; error condition mismatches)\r\n# Proprietary and fickle web-service-stack response processing to convert ERROR carrying but otherwise legitimate response messages to an Exception.\r\n\r\nThe use of faults would enable a number of sane and altogether good things to happen:\r\n# Generic error handling in web-services-stack across services (reduce test surface; uses existing and working implementation)\r\n# Clarity of fault condition, code, and detail\r\n# Makes fault types explicit in the API document\r\n\r\nThe below snippet (from axis2c-src-1.6.0/src/core/engine/disp_checker.c:251) is used by the service dispatcher in Axis2c to report \"operation not found\" errors and produces a proper SOAP fault which the CLC can parse properly:\r\n{code}\r\n251     if (!op)\r\n252     {\r\n253         AXIS2_LOG_INFO(env->log,\r\n254                        \"Operation Not found. Endpoint reference is :\r\n%s\",\r\n255                        (address) ? address : \"NULL\");\r\n256         if (axis2_msg_ctx_get_is_soap_11(msg_ctx, env))\r\n257         {\r\n258             soap_version = AXIOM_SOAP11;\r\n259             fault_code =\r\n260                 AXIOM_SOAP_DEFAULT_NAMESPACE_PREFIX \":\"\r\n261                 AXIOM_SOAP11_FAULT_CODE_RECEIVER;\r\n262         }\r\n263         else\r\n264         {\r\n265             fault_code =\r\n266                 AXIOM_SOAP_DEFAULT_NAMESPACE_PREFIX \":\"\r\n267                 AXIOM_SOAP12_SOAP_FAULT_VALUE_RECEIVER;\r\n268         }\r\n269 \r\n270 \r\n271         soap_envelope =\r\n272             axiom_soap_envelope_create_default_soap_envelope(env,\r\nsoap_version);\r\n273         soap_body = axiom_soap_envelope_get_body(soap_envelope, env);\r\n274         soap_fault =\r\n275             axiom_soap_fault_create_default_fault(env, soap_body,\r\nfault_code,\r\n276                                                   \"Operation Not Found\",\r\n277                                                   soap_version);\r\n278 \r\n279         wsa_action = (axis2_char_t *)axis2_msg_ctx_get_wsa_action\r\n(msg_ctx,\r\n280                                                                    env);\r\n281         sprintf (exception, \"Operation Not Found, Endpoint referance\r\naddress is %s and wsa\\\r\n282  actions is %s\", address, wsa_action);\r\n283 \r\n284         axiom_soap_fault_set_exception (soap_fault, env, exception);\r\n285         axis2_msg_ctx_set_fault_soap_envelope(msg_ctx, env,\r\nsoap_envelope);\r\n286         return AXIS2_FAILURE;\r\n287     }\r\n288     return AXIS2_SUCCESS;\r\n{code}","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"summary":"Axis2c web-services should generate soapfaults on errors","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=decker","name":"decker","key":"decker","accountId":"557058:518b1ab0-12c2-4e72-b694-6c07036941a8","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a84cbf1ecec07d9320b42ae4fc90ccce?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Ddecker%26avatarId%3D16203%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a84cbf1ecec07d9320b42ae4fc90ccce?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Ddecker%26avatarId%3D16203%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a84cbf1ecec07d9320b42ae4fc90ccce?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Ddecker%26avatarId%3D16203%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/a84cbf1ecec07d9320b42ae4fc90ccce?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2